# Zod Validation Standards

## Context

- This rule applies to all TypeScript and TSX files in the project
- Runtime validation ensures data integrity beyond compile-time type checking

## Requirements

- Always use Zod schemas to validate external data (API responses, form inputs)
- Always define Zod schemas for complex data structures
- Always derive TypeScript types from Zod schemas using z.infer<typeof schema>
- Always handle validation errors gracefully
- Always use Zod transformations for data normalization when appropriate
